&lt;img src="http://mashable.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/07/lenny.png" alt="" /&gt;</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The British lawmakers and ISPs are now seriously mulling the idea of a <a href="http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/music-industry-to-tax-downloaders-875757.html" target="_blank">preemptive piracy tax</a>; a yearly fee that would be imposed on everyone who uses the Internet - say, 30 pounds - collected by the ISPs, and given back to the artists. </p>
