		<description>&lt;p&gt;Facebook has announced the “&lt;a href="http://developers.new.facebook.com/greatapps.php" target="_blank"&gt;Great Apps Program&lt;/a&gt;,” a developer offering that gives certain applications “greater visibility on Facebook, earlier access to new features and more feedback from Facebook.”  The initial partners for Great Apps are &lt;a href="http://apps.new.facebook.com/causes/about" target="_blank"&gt;Causes&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://www.ilike.com/" target="_blank"&gt;iLike&lt;/a&gt;.  It will open to everyone else in September.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For everyone else, Facebook is launching the “&lt;a href="http://developers.new.facebook.com/verification.php" target="_blank"&gt;Application Verification Program&lt;/a&gt;” – also available in September – that will allow developers to receive official certification from the social network and gain added visibility.    According to Facebook, the program will “offer extra assurances to help users identify applications they can trust &amp;#8212; applications that are secure, respectful and transparent, and have demonstrated commitment to compliance with Platform policies.”  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additionally, Facebook has announced a fresh $10 million that they will infuse into a second round of the fbFund.  Simultaneously, they are announcing the following winners of the first round of funding for application developers:  CourseFeed by Classtop, GoalCamp, HotBerry, J2Play, LuckyCal, MyListo, Podclass, Trazzler, and &lt;a href="http://mashable.com/2007/04/15/zimride/"&gt;Zimride Carpool App&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
