		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.mashable.com/images/facebooklogofresh.PNG"/></p>
<p>Facebook has announced the “<a href="http://developers.new.facebook.com/greatapps.php" target="_blank">Great Apps Program</a>,” a developer offering that gives certain applications “greater visibility on Facebook, earlier access to new features and more feedback from Facebook.”  The initial partners for Great Apps are <a href="http://apps.new.facebook.com/causes/about" target="_blank">Causes</a> and <a href="http://www.ilike.com/" target="_blank">iLike</a>.  It will open to everyone else in September.</p>
<p>For everyone else, Facebook is launching the “<a href="http://developers.new.facebook.com/verification.php" target="_blank">Application Verification Program</a>” – also available in September – that will allow developers to receive official certification from the social network and gain added visibility.  <img src="http://mashable.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/07/facebookf8c.gif" align="right"/>  According to Facebook, the program will “offer extra assurances to help users identify applications they can trust &#8212; applications that are secure, respectful and transparent, and have demonstrated commitment to compliance with Platform policies.”  </p>
<p>Additionally, Facebook has announced a fresh $10 million that they will infuse into a second round of the fbFund.  Simultaneously, they are announcing the following winners of the first round of funding for application developers:  CourseFeed by Classtop, GoalCamp, HotBerry, J2Play, LuckyCal, MyListo, Podclass, Trazzler, and <a href="http://mashable.com/2007/04/15/zimride/">Zimride Carpool App</a>.</p>
